Equivalent fractions

1. Equivalent fractions


ID is: 1990 Seed is: 5853

Types of fractions

Is the following fraction a proper, improper, or mixed fraction: 258258?

Answer:
HINT: <no title>
[−0 points ⇒ 1 / 1 points left]

If you do not remember the meaning of the three types of fractions, take a look in your notes or your book for definitions or examples!

STEP: <no title>
[−1 point ⇒ 0 / 1 points left]

Here is a summary of the three types of fractions:

  • Proper fractions: fractions which are less than one; the numerator is always less than the denominator.
  • Improper fractions: fractions which are greater than or equal to one; the numerator is larger than or equal to the denominator.
  • Mixed fractions (mixed numbers): a number which has an integer part and a fraction part; the fraction part must be a proper fraction (less than one).

258258 has an Integer part at the front (the 22) followed by a proper fraction (the 5858). Therefore it is a mixed fraction.

Identifying equivalent fractions

Are the following fractions equivalent fractions or not?

12=4812=48
Answer:
HINT: <no title>
[−0 points ⇒ 1 / 1 points left]
Equivalent fractions must be equal to each other! For example, 6363 and 105105 are equivalent because they are both equal to 22.
STEP: <no title>
[−1 point ⇒ 0 / 1 points left]

Equivalent fractions are the same number written in two different ways. It is exactly the same when we write 44 or 4141. Another example is 55 or 5.05.0. The numbers are the same - they only look different.

You can see this best with pictures. The rectangle on the top shows the fraction 1212; the rectangle on the bottom shows 4848.

You can see from the picture that the fractions are the same size - the shaded area is the same. Therefore 1212 and 4848 are equivalent.

Equivalent fractions always have proportional numbers in them. In this case, the factor of proportionality is 44. You can see this factor in the diagram because each of the pieces on the top rectangle has been split into 44 pieces in the rectangle on the bottom.

The correct choice from the list is "Yes, they are equivalent."

    Answer:
    HINT: <no title>
    [−0 points ⇒ 1 / 1 points left]

    A fraction shows how many parts there are in a whole. The denominator of the fraction tells you how many pieces are in the whole: check which of the diagrams is divided into 22 pieces.

    STEP: <no title>
    [−1 point ⇒ 0 / 1 points left]

    A fraction tells you how parts there are out of a whole. For example, if it rains 33 days in one week, that is 33 rainy days out of 77. The fraction for rainy days that week looks like this: 3737.

    When we draw a fraction as a picture, we must break the object (in this case, a circle) into the total number of pieces (the denominator). Then we shade in however many parts are in the numerator.

    The correct picture for 1212 must be a shape which is divided into 22 equal parts; 11 of them must be shaded.

    The correct picture for the fraction 1212 is picture C.

    Submit your answer as:

  2. Based on the correct picture above, is 1212 closer to zero or one (or exactly in the middle)?

    Answer:
    HINT: <no title>
    [−0 points ⇒ 1 / 1 points left]

    Use the picture to decide. For example, if less than half of the shape is shaded, then the number is closer to zero.

    STEP: <no title>
    [−1 point ⇒ 0 / 1 points left]

    Draw a line across the picture to cut the shape in two equal parts (in half). Is the shading less than half of the shape or more than half of the shape?

    You can see that the shaded part is the same size as the unshaded part. 1212 is exactly halfway between zero and one.

    We can also think of the fraction itself to answer this question: 1212 means "11 out of 22." For example, imagine taking 11 apple out of 22 apples sitting on a table. That leaves 11 apple on the table! Taking 11 and leaving 11 means that you took half of the apples, exactly halfway from zero to one.

    The correct answer is that 1212 is exactly in the middle.

STEP: Proportionality factor
[−1 point ⇒ 1 / 2 points left]

Equivalent fractions are the same number written in two different ways. It is exactly the same when we write 44 or 4141. You can also write 55 or 5,05,0. The numbers are the same - they only look different.

The proportionality factor is the number which connects the numerator and denominator in one fraction with the numerator and denominator in the other fraction to make sure that they are equal. In this case, we must find the proportionality factor from the denominators (because 𝑥x is in the numerator!).

The denominators shown are 33 and 1212: this means that the proportionality factor must be 44, because 3×4=123×4=12.

The fractions here have a proportionality factor of 44.

STEP: Finding 𝑥x
[−1 point ⇒ 0 / 2 points left]

Once we know the proportionality factor, finding 𝑥x comes quickly: just multiply!

To get the value of 𝑥x, we need to use the proportionality factor: 𝑥×4=4x×4=4. The answer is 𝑥=1x=1.

You can check this out with pictures: the circle on the left shows the fraction 1313; the circle on the right shows 412412. You can see that the shaded areas are the same: "11 out of 33" is the same fraction as "44 out of 1212." That is what "equivalent fractions" are!

The value of 𝑥x is 11.

Changing from mixed fractions to improper fractions

Rewrite the mixed fraction here as an improper fraction.

312312
Answer:
fraction
2 attempts remaining
HINT: <no title>
[−0 points ⇒ 2 / 2 points left]

The first thing to do is to multiply the denominator by the integer value in the front of the mixed number! After that, you must add the numerator from the fraction part of the mixed number.

STEP: <no title>
[−2 points ⇒ 0 / 2 points left]

You have the mixed number 312312 and you must write it as an improper fraction. An improper fraction is a fraction with a numerator larger than the denominator.

The method for converting a mixed fraction into an improper fraction can be called "toilet maths." Yes, that's right! The picture below shows how it works.

"Toilet maths" goes in a circle, like when you flush a toilet. Start at the denominator; then follow the blue arrow around and multiply by the integer in the front; then continue following the purple arrow and add the numerator. In other words, do this: 2×3+1=72×3+1=7. The toilet maths calculation gives you the numerator of the improper fraction.

Once we have the numerator, we must write the improper fraction using the same denominator as the mixed number, which gives us the answer:

312=72312=72

It is important to know that these are simply two ways to write the same number!

The correct improper fraction is 7272.

Consider the two numbers 4.84.8 and 4.14.1. Which of the numbers is larger?

Choose the correct symbol from the choices below to show which number is larger, or if the numbers are equal.

Answer:

4.84.8 4.14.1

HINT: <no title>
[−0 points ⇒ 1 / 1 points left]

Imagine where these numbers sit on the number line (or just draw it quickly if that will help you). Remember that whichever number is on the right side is the larger number.

STEP: <no title>
[−1 point ⇒ 0 / 1 points left]

We have two numbers, and we must compare them using the inequality symbols to show which number is the bigger one (and which is the smaller one).

Let's graph these two numbers on the number line: that will make it easy to see which one is larger! Do not forget that the decimal numbers tell us to divide things into tens; so for example, 4.84.8 is 88 out of 1010 steps from 44 to 55. The picture below shows the ten little steps between each integer.

When you see two numbers on the number line, the one on the right is always greater than the one on the left. Therefore, 4.84.8 must be the bigger number.

Remember that the inequality symbol always opens to the larger number, like an animal eating the larger snack! It is like this:

Therefore, the correct option from the list is ">>" which looks like this in the end: 4.8>4.14.8>4.1. (In words, this means, "4.84.8 is greater than 4.14.1")

Answer: The number 4.54.5 is at: .
HINT: <no title>
[−0 points ⇒ 1 / 1 points left]

Remember that decimal numbers divide things into ten parts. The number 4.54.5 means 44 plus 5 out of 1010 between 44 and 55.

STEP: <no title>
[−1 point ⇒ 0 / 1 points left]

We need to find the location of 4.54.5 on the number line. We know straight away that it must be between 44 and 55... but where in between?

Remember that decimal numbers divide things into tenths: 4.54.5 means the number that is 55 out of 1010 spaces from 44 to 55. In your mind, divide the number line into ten equal little bits between each of the integers: the decimal value tells you how many of these little bits to use when you find the number! (These little bits are shown in the picture below.)

The number 4.54.5 is 55 steps out of 1010 from 44 - exactly in the middle of 44 and 55!

The point which agrees with these facts is Point C.

The number 4.54.5 is located at Point C.
